ion%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20at%20what%20was%20still%20Twitter%2C%20some%20of%20the%20billionaire's%20biggest%20fans%20hailed%20the%20move%20as%20a%20new%20era%20of%20free%2C%20unfiltered%2C%20and%20unmoderated%20speech%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReplacing%20the%20people%20burdened%20with%20the%20difficult%20task%20of%20tackling%20misinformation%20was%20going%20to%20be%20an%20existing%20feature%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-rebrand-x-brands-slow-to-switch-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%2C%20now%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-renames-birdwatch-community-notes-touts-improving-accuracy-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBirdWatch%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fact-checking%20program%20that%20relies%20on%20user%20input.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBirdwatch%20(soon%20to%20be%20renamed%20Community%20Notes)%20has%20incredible%20potential%20for%20improving%20information%20accuracy%20on%20Twitter!%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said%20last%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20and%20fans%20of%20the%20new%20Twitter%20have%20stood%20by%20the%20feature%2C%20arguing%20that%20it's%20a%20preferred%20alternative%20to%20removing%20misinformation%20altogether.%20But%20even%20X%20fanboys%20have%20had%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20shortcomings%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-dorsey-criticize-elon-musk-rename-birdwatch-community-notes-boring-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECommunity%20Notes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20critics%20have%20pointed%20out%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happened-with-elon-musk-twitter-timeline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk's%20takeover%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConservative%20blogger%20Ian%20Miles%20Cheong%2C%20who%20regularly%20responds%20to%20Musk's%20posts%20and%20has%20about%20865%2C000%20followers%20on%20X%2C%20likes%20to%20highlight%20when%20Democratic%20politicians%2C%20mainstream%20news%20outlets%2C%20and%20posts%20that%20generally%20appear%20to%20support%20left-wing%20views%20are%20checked%20by%20Community%20Notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCommunity%20Notes%20does%20not%20miss%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20has%20said%20in%20multiple%20variations%20%E2%80%94%20until%20it%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20an%20X%20user%20who%20appeared%20to%20support%20the%20idea%20of%20decolonization%20in%20Western%20societies%2C%20the%20blogger%20wrote%20in%20response%3A%20%26quot%3BThese%20people%20want%20us%20dead.%20They%20make%20no%20secret%20of%20it.%20It's%20time%20to%20wake%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Community%20Note%20soon%20appeared%20under%20his%20post%3A%20%26quot%3BIan%20Miles%20Cheong%20is%20Malaysian%20and%20has%20never%20been%20to%20the%20US.%20Malaysia%20is%20not%20a%20Western%20nation%20and%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20as%20somewhere%20between%2063%25%20and%2075%25%20Muslim%20population%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20survey.%20He%20would%20be%20closer%20to%20the%20'they'%20than%20the%20'us'%20in%20this%20statement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheong%20has%20since%20taken%20down%20the%20post%20but%20called%20the%20note%20%26quot%3Binsane%2C%26quot%3B%20claiming%20that%20he%20has%20visited%20the%20US%20multiple%20times%20and%20accused%20the%20Community%20Notes%20feature%20of%20being%20gamed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20realize%20CN%20(Community%20Notes)%20could%20be%20used%20to%20troll%20people%20you%20disagree%20with%20politically%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheong%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20email%20that%20he%20doesn't%20feel%20Community%20Notes%20is%20unreliable%20%26quot%3Bmost%20of%20the%20time%26quot%3B%20and%20that%2C%20although%20it%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Boccasionally%20gamed%20by%20the%20masses%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20feature%20does%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20job%26quot%3B%20at%20tackling%20misinformation%20and%20adding%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20most%20of%20his%20frustration%20about%20the%20notes%20is%20when%20he%20feels%20%26quot%3Bno%20context%20is%20necessary%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20satirical%20meme.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECritics%20are%20skeptical%20of%20Community%20Notes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20may%20argue%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20no%20X%20user%2C%20including%20Musk%20himself%2C%20is%20immune%20to%20a%20correction%20from%20Community%20Notes%20is%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20feature's%20capability%2C%20but%20critics%20have%20repeatedly%20pointed%20out%20the%20flaws%20of%20the%20system%20behind%20the%20feature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20at%20Twitter%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fgraphics%2F2022-twitter-birdwatch-community-notes-misinformation-politics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20feature%2C%20as%20it%20was%20designed%20at%20the%20time%2C%20can't%20address%20divisive%20posts%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20clearly%20lies%2C%20because%20a%20note%20needs%20consensus%20from%20users%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum.%20Data%20showed%20that%20about%2096%25%20of%20fact-checking%20notes%20contributed%20by%20Community%20Notes%20did%20not%20end%20up%20being%20posted%20for%20the%20public%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHalf%20a%20year%20later%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.poynter.org%2Ffact-checking%2F2023%2Fwhy-twitters-community-notes-feature-mostly-fails-to-combat-misinformation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPoynter%20Institute's%20MediaWise%20Director%20Alex%20Mahadevan%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20the%20program%20still%20suffers%20from%20visibility%20issues%20because%20of%20how%20Community%20Notes%20operates.%20Typical%20X%20users%20could%20only%20see%20about%208.5%25%20of%20the%20total%20notes%20that%20have%20been%20contributed%20by%20participating%20users%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20system%20has%20caused%20X%20to%20be%20slower%20to%20act%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-social-media-misinformation-swamping-fake-news-trust-safety-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eposts%20related%20to%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20broke%20out%20in%20October%20and%20have%20been%20debunked%20but%20viewed%20by%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20users%20without%20an%20appendaged%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fx-community-notes-disinformation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWired%3C%2Fa%3E%20investigation%20published%20in%20October%2C%20which%20included%20ex-Twitter%20employees%20and%20a%20current%20Community%20Notes%20contributor%2C%20also%20found%20that%20Community%20Notes%20is%20vulnerable%20to%20manipulation%20by%20outside%20players%2C%20the%20notes%20themselves%20can%20be%20a%20source%20of%20misinformation%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20the%20approval%20process%20behind%20notes%20is%20still%20murky.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EElon%20Musk's%20biggest%20fans%20voice%20concerns%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Musk's%20strongest%20supporters%20who%20have%20bought%20into%20the%20X%20owner's%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffree-speech-absolutist-elon-musk-censors-employees-critics-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bfree%20speech%20absolutist%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20vision%20on%20the%20platform%20have%20argued%20about%20Community%20Notes'%20limitations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20investor%20David%20Sacks%2C%20who%20hailed%20%26quot%3BFree%20Speech%20is%20back%20in%20America%26quot%3B%20after%20X%20reinstated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-said-donald-trumps-twitter-account-will-be-reinstated-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump's%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20November%2C%20said%20the%20feature